Heat oven to 425 degrees F. Place salmon on a small baking sheet. Season salmon with salt and pepper and spread with 1 tablespoon of chipotle raspberry sauce. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Remove skin from salmon and cut into 4 pieces. Mix remaining chipotle raspberry sauce with mayonnaise. Serve salmon on buns topped with spoonful of mayonnaise mixture.